Researchers and practitioners will be able to find in this handbook state-of-the-art information on typical and atypical development of language and communication (dis)abilities across the human lifespan from infancy to the aging brain, covering all major clinical disorders and conditions in various social and communicative contexts, such as spoken and written language and discourse, literacy issues, bilingualism, and socio-economic status.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 04. Okt 2022) 0aCommunicative disorders. 4aAngewandte Linguistik. 4aKommunikation. 4aStörung. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aApplied Linguistics.  aCommunication Disorders.  aDevelopmental Disabilities.  aLiteracy.1 aAksu-Koç, Ayhan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAktan-Erciyes, Aslı, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAram, Dorit, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aArmon-Lotem, Sharon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAssal, Frédéric, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAteş, Beyza Ş., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBaayen, Harald, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBar-On, Amalia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBar-On, Amalia, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBat-El, Outi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBen-David, Avivit, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBerman, Ruth A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBiedermann, Britta, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/c